  "cooked": "<p>I\u2019ve also been confused at the lack of docs. Might be good to at least update the wiki with the extra detail? sipa\u2019s PR is:</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox githubpullrequest\" data-onebox-src=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/524\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/524\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"github-row\">\n\n\n\n    <div class=\"github-icon-container\" title=\"Pull Request\">\n      <svg width=\"60\" height=\"60\" class=\"github-icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 12 16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11 11.28V5c-.03-.78-.34-1.47-.94-2.06C9.46 2.35 8.78 2.03 8 2H7V0L4 3l3 3V4h1c.27.02.48.11.69.31.21.2.3.42.31.69v6.28A1.993 1.993 0 0 0 10 15a1.993 1.993 0 0 0 1-3.72zm-1 2.92c-.66 0-1.2-.55-1.2-1.2 0-.65.55-1.2 1.2-1.2.65 0 1.2.55 1.2 1.2 0 .65-.55 1.2-1.2 1.2zM4 3c0-1.11-.89-2-2-2a1.993 1.993 0 0 0-1 3.72v6.56A1.993 1.993 0 0 0 2 15a1.993 1.993 0 0 0 1-3.72V4.72c.59-.34 1-.98 1-1.72zm-.8 10c0 .66-.55 1.2-1.2 1.2-.65 0-1.2-.55-1.2-1.2 0-.65.55-1.2 1.2-1.2.65 0 1.2.55 1.2 1.2zM2 4.2C1.34 4.2.8 3.65.8 3c0-.65.55-1.2 1.2-1.2.65 0 1.2.55 1.2 1.2 0 .65-.55 1.2-1.2 1.2z\"></path></svg>\n    </div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-info-container\">\n\n\n\n      <h4>\n        <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/524\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sign and verify message with bitcoin address</a>\n      </h4>\n\n    <div class=\"branches\">\n      <code>bitcoin:master</code> \u2190 <code>sipa:signandverif</code>\n    </div>\n\n      <div class=\"github-info\">\n        <div class=\"date\">\n          opened <span class=\"discourse-local-date\" data-format=\"ll\" data-date=\"2011-09-20\" data-time=\"15:26:43\" data-timezone=\"UTC\">03:26PM - 20 Sep 11 UTC</span>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"user\">\n          <a href=\"https://github.com/sipa\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n            <img alt=\"sipa\" src=\"https://delvingbitcoin.org/uploads/default/original/1X/c614277d4450410b09ebd39a0f22c7b8e75e9cde.jpeg\" class=\"onebox-avatar-inline\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" data-dominant-color=\"7E757B\">\n            sipa\n          </a>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"lines\" title=\"8 commits changed 6 files with 372 additions and 38 deletions\">\n          <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/524/files\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n            <span class=\"added\">+372</span>\n            <span class=\"removed\">-38</span>\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-row\">\n    <p class=\"github-body-container\">This is a reworked version of #183\n\nAdds two RPC commands:\n- signmessage [addres<span class=\"show-more-container\"><a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/524\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"show-more\">\u2026</a></span><span class=\"excerpt hidden\">s] [message]: create a base64-encoded signature string\n- verifymessage [address] [signature] [message]: verify whether a signature string is valid\n\nThe signature string contains both the ECDSA pubkey and signature, to allow address-based verification.\nVerifymessage simply returns true or false.\n\nThis pull request also contains a full inline base64 encoded and decoder, replacing the openssl-based code. The decoder is based on JoelKatz' base64 decoder from #430.</span></p>\n  </div>\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>Forum discussion linked from there at <a href=\"https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=6428.0;all\">https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=6428.0;all</a> is probably also interesting.</p>",
